# GoogleService-Info-Dev.plist

This file is git-ignored. To set up Firebase for development:

1. Go to the Firebase console (https://console.firebase.google.com)
2. Open the "wevibe-dev" Firebase project
3. Go to Project Settings > General > Your apps > iOS app
4. Download GoogleService-Info.plist
5. Rename it to GoogleService-Info-Dev.plist
6. Place it in this directory: frontend/iOS/WeVibe/Firebase/

DO NOT add this file to Xcode's Copy Bundle Resources phase.
The build script (Run Script phase) copies it automatically.
